The paper deals with testing properties of functions, which is a common theme in computer science theory. The focus is on testing unateness of real-valued functions, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses information theory techniques to analyze the query complexity of the testers, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT. The use of adaptivity in the testers is a key aspect of the paper, which could make it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
